Society for Savings said it will offerup to 100 mln dlrs of medium-term notes with maturites of oneto five years through Goldman, Sachs and Co and Shearson LehmanBrothers Inc.    The notes will be supported by an irrevocable letter ofcredit by the Federal Home Loan Bank of Boston. Each note willbear interest at a fixed-rate or variable rate formulaestablished at the time of issuance, Society for Savings said.    Bankers Trust Co will act as fiscal and paying agent.Non-redeemable to maturity, the notes will be issued only inregistered form and in minimum denomiations of 100,000 dlrs. Reuter&#3;